ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'පරිශ්‍රීලකයින්' (parishreelakayin) is a less common and potentially inaccurate rendering of 'users'. The standard term for 'users' in Sinhala is 'භාවිතරයන්' (bhavitakarayan) or 'පරිශීලකයින්' (parishilakayin).

The Slovak translation 'Používatelia sa nenašli' is a literal translation and sounds unnatural. A more natural and idiomatic Slovak phrase would be 'Neboli nájdení používatelia' or 'Nenašli sa žiadni používatelia'.
The translation "Ниједан корисник пронађен" is a literal translation and not the most natural way to say "No users found" in Serbian. It sounds awkward.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: A more natural translation would be "Нема корисника пронађено" or "Ништа корисници нису пронађени".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Nijedan korisnik pronađen' is a literal translation but sounds somewhat unnatural in Serbian. A more idiomatic and natural phrasing would be preferred.
